parameters.text:
=Given the following details about a job posting, identify the company's primary website domain name (e.g., "google.com"). Use the company name, job description, LinkedIn URL, and job URL to determine the most accurate domain, including the correct top-level domain (e.g., .com, .co, .org). If the URLs contain the domain, prioritize that information. If no clear domain can be determined, return "unknown". Return only the domain name as a plain string (e.g., "example.com") without any additional text, quotes, or JSON structure.

Company Name: {{ $json.companyName }}
Job Description: {{ $json.description }}
LinkedIn URL: {{ $json.companyUrl }}
Job URL: {{ $json.jobUrl }}

Output only the domain name.
